**`makeCacheKey` uses `JSON.stringify`** (`server/search.ts:146`)

Called on every cached search request. `JSON.stringify` with 10 fields allocates a new object and serializes it. A simple template string is ~10x faster:

```ts
function makeCacheKey(...params): string {
    return `${query}|${tab}|${safesearch}|${offset}|${freshness ?? ''}|${country ?? ''}|${filterAds}|${blockAds}|${blockTrackers}|${count}`;
}
```

