**`hostname()` in `AiAnswer.svelte` recomputed per render** (`AiAnswer.svelte:12`)

The `hostname()` function creates a `new URL()` for each source citation on every render. With Svelte 5, derive it once:

```svelte
let hostnames = $derived(sources.map(s => {
    try { return new URL(s.url).hostname.replace(/^www\./, ''); }
    catch { return s.url; }
}));
```

---

**`AiAnswer.svelte` fetch has no debounce** (`AiAnswer.svelte:21`)

The `$effect` fires on every `query` change. If search results update query while typing, this fires once per keystroke. Add a short debounce:

```svelte
$effect(() => {
    const q = query;
    if (!q || tab !== 'web') { answer = null; sources = []; loading = false; return; }

    loading = true;
    const controller = new AbortController();
    const timer = setTimeout(() => {
        fetch(`/api/answer?q=${encodeURIComponent(q)}`, { signal: controller.signal })
            .then(...)
    }, 300);  // debounce

    return () => { clearTimeout(timer); controller.abort(); };
});
```

---

**Lazy-only pruning in `security.ts`, `altcha.ts`, and `server/search.ts`**

All three in-memory Maps (`clients`, `usedSignatures`, `rateLimitBuckets`) are only pruned when their respective write functions are called. On a long-running server with traffic that drops off, entries can accumulate indefinitely.

```ts
// Add a periodic sweep — run once at module load
setInterval(() => {
    const now = Date.now();
    prune(now);  // or pruneUsed / pruneRateLimitBuckets
}, 5 * 60_000);
```

This is low-risk on serverless (instances are short-lived) but matters for `node` deploys.

